text: Tracie Davis (born May 6, 1970 in Jacksonville, Florida) is an American politician and former teacher who currently serves as the representative for Florida House of Representatives District 13 as a member of the Democratic Party. After former Democratic representative Reggie Fullwood pleaded guilty to two counts of federal fraud, Davis was selected by the Duval County Democratic Party to replace him on the ticket.https://www.myfloridahouse.gov/Sections/Representatives/details.aspx?MemberId=4651&LegislativeTermId;=87 Florida House Prior to her run, she was a special education teacher for Duval County Public Schools, and subsequently worked as the supervisor of elections. She holds education degrees from University of North Florida and Edward Waters College.http://jacksonville.com/opinion/2015-02-26/story/meet-candidate- tracie-davis Jacksonville ==References== Category:Members of the Florida House of Representatives Category:Living people Category:People from Jacksonville, Florida Category:Florida Democrats Category:University of North Florida alumni Category:Edward Waters College alumni Category:1970 births Category:Women state legislators in Florida
